Class DefaultJMSTransformer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.jms.DefaultJMSTransformer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFromMessageTransformer, IMessageTransformer, IToMessageTransformer, IMessageProcessorEventTransformer

    public class DefaultJMSTransformer
extends Object
implements IMessageTransformer, IMessageProcessorEventTransformer
    This transformer converts Catalys messages to and from JMS messages.

      • toMessage

        public IFIXMessage toMessage(Object sourceJmsMessage,
                             IFIXMessage targetFIXMessage,
                             boolean dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData)
                      throws IllegalArgumentException
        Create a Catalys message from a JMS message.
        Specified by:
        toMessage in interface IToMessageTransformer
        Parameters:
        sourceJmsMessage - a JMS Object, can be a javax.jms.BytesMessage or javax.jms.TextMessage or javax.jms.ObjectMessage.
        targetFIXMessage - target FIX message (transformed from jmxMessage)
        dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData - True to indicate that no special treatment is to be given to raw data and their associated length fields (that is, they are expected to conform to regular FIX field content and in particular the data field should not contain FIX SOH), false to treat the data field as opaque and use its preceding length field to determine its length.
        Returns:
        IFIXMessage target message (transformed from source)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given jmxMessage is not supported for transformation.
